      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the highest scoring Scrabble words ending in ER?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "QUIZZER (34 pts), QUICKER (22 pts), and JINXER (20 pts) lead the pack. More commonly playable high-scorers include WHACKER (19 pts), FOXIER (16 pts), JOKER (16 pts), and HEXER (15 pts). The -ER suffix adds only 2 points but unlocks agent nouns and comparatives from existing roots." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does the ER suffix work strategically in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ER serves two grammatical functions: it creates agent nouns (PLAY to PLAYER, TEACH to TEACHER) and comparatives (QUICK to QUICKER, FAST to FASTER). Both types are valid extensions of words already on the board. ER is also a powerful hook — adding ER to FARM makes FARMER, scoring the full word plus crosswords." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you add ER to any adjective or verb in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Not universally. Most one-syllable adjectives accept -ER (TALL to TALLER, FAST to FASTER), and many verbs form agent nouns (PLAY to PLAYER, SING to SINGER). However, some don't work — you can't play BEAUTIFULER. Always verify with a word checker. Common exceptions include multi-syllable adjectives and irregular comparatives." }
      }
